{
  "Exponential growth uses the formula:": "",
  "A = P(1+r)^t": "",
  "A = Prt": "",
  "A = P(1-r)^t": "",
  "A = P - rt": "",
  "Exponential growth uses A = P(1+r)^t where the (1+r) base is greater than 1, causing the value to increase at an accelerating rate over time.": "",
  "Exponential decay uses the formula:": "",
  "A = Pe^rt": "",
  "Exponential decay uses A = P(1-r)^t where the (1-r) base is between 0 and 1, causing the value to decrease at a decelerating rate over time.": "",
