  "What does 'exponential growth' mean?": "",
  "Growth by the same dollar amount each period": "",
  "Growth where the rate of increase is proportional to the current value, causing accelerating increase over time": "",
  "Growth that slows down over time": "",
  "Growth that occurs in a straight line": "",
  "Exponential growth means the amount of increase each period is proportional to the current size, creating a compounding effect where larger values generate even larger increases.": "",
