  "A value that increases then decreases": "",
  "A value dropping to zero immediately": "",
  "A value decreasing by a constant percentage each period, so the rate of decrease slows as the value shrinks": "",
  "A value decreasing by the same dollar amount each period": "",
  "Exponential decay means a quantity loses a constant fraction of its value each period. The absolute decrease gets smaller over time because the remaining amount gets smaller.": "",
